    <title type="html"><![CDATA[[THOUGHTS] the End of Glossy Design Era]]></title>
    <link href="http://nicnocquee.com/blog/2012/12/03/thoughts-the-end-of-glossy-design-era/"/>
    <updated>2012-12-03T17:20:00+09:00</updated>
    <id>http://nicnocquee.com/blog/2012/12/03/thoughts-the-end-of-glossy-design-era</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.gogeeks.tv/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/iphone-icons.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>As far as I know, Apple made the glossy design popular with the iPhone icons. But in recent years, seems like app designers/devs started to embrace the flat icons.</p>

<!-- more -->


<p><img src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_medntudVmz1qzxzwwo1_500.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>Some famous apps like Flipboard:</p>

<p><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Flipboard icon" /></p>

<p>Evernote:</p>

<p><img src="https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSC4IH9aU5BRgtE-w67CB1mfUUl3KFk-l4ZyQQopBit_VLGluWx" alt="" /></p>

<p>And even <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/jp/app/monoco/id539376693?mt=8">Monoco</a>, the app I&#8217;m working on!</p>

<p><img src="http://a2.mzstatic.com/us/r1000/119/Purple/v4/81/83/34/8183345d-3e42-43e3-9c34-1951d36dc5d6/mzm.umiabhlc.175x175-75.jpg" alt="" /></p>

<p>I noticed this trend started with Microsoft&#8217;s not-to-be-called-Metro style for Windows 8 (or RT?). Maybe it started even before, but it if this is true, Microsoft has done something right this time.</p>
]]></content>
